				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ N=\mathrm{SQ}\ast \frac{1}{\mathrm{ssf}}\ast \frac{1}{\mathrm{asf}}\ast \frac{1}{\mathrm{tsf}} $$\end{document}N=SQ∗1ssf∗1asf∗1tsfwhere SQ represents the number of neurons counted in all optically sampled fields of the hippocampus, ssf is the section sampling fraction, asf is the area sampling fraction, and tsf is the thickness sampling fraction.
